Later, the presidency of Peru sent an email in media with the "final statement" of the summit, but it was about the speech of the president Humala and not of the official document which concluded the summit.
Last October, Peru was the guest of the 3rd summit America of the South-country Arab (ASPA) and, at this occasion, good that the press asks for it insistently, it had not broadcast either the statement called also Statement of Lima, as it had before been announced.
On the official site of the ASPA, it is possible to prove that the document was published in last March.
