Among adopted agreements, he mentioned that the countries of Unasur would set up "important steps to hit the mark of South American citizenship by the development of agreements on residence permits".
He informed that actions would be set up to improve "cooperation in the struggle against urban insecurity and against international organised crime, actions for a better accessibility in medicaments, access to the Internet cheap in its entirety of South America, and to assess in a joint and efficient way risks of natural disasters".
With Europe in crisis, "economic strengthening (from Latin America) does not owe to have a triumphalist matrix but must help to augment our productive matrix and to foresee a better future for our populations", concluded the president Humala.
"We decided to favour a group of 31 emblematic plans which improve the connection of the areas of South America, especially in the rural and border zones by joining our countries and by generating new economic circuits", declared the Peruvian president during a speech.
